# Vendored framework SOURCE — install.sh always ships these framework-namespace files fresh; a
# consumer never authors `eslint-rules-local/`, `packages/core/hooks/`, or `scripts/audit-r4.ts`.
# They ship formatted to THIS framework's Prettier config (printWidth 80, singleQuote, no plugins);
# a consumer with its OWN .prettierrc rejects the same bytes — the #531 config-mismatch root cause
# (NOT a Prettier version skew: identical bytes are clean under our config and dirty under the
# consumer's). They are not the consumer's code to format-check, so ignore them config-agnostically.
#
# Framework CONFIG files the consumer MIGHT already own (eslint.config.mjs, vitest.config.ts,
# tsconfig.json, .dependency-cruiser.cjs, stryker.config.json, .lintstagedrc.json, the CI workflows)
# are handled CONDITIONALLY in install.sh (`ignore_shipped_configs`): each is ignored ONLY when
# install actually SHIPPED it fresh — never when copy_safe kept a consumer-authored one. That keeps
# a consumer's own config format-checked instead of silently hiding it. (GH #531 reopen)
eslint-rules-local/*.ts
packages/core/hooks/**
scripts/audit-r4.ts

